Interface KWHashMap<K,​V>

Type Parameters:
K - Key
V - Value
All Known Implementing Classes:
HashtableChain, HashtableCoalesced, HashtableOpen, HashtableTree
public interface KWHashMap<K,​V>
An HashMap interface which contains some methods of HashMap Data Structure

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    V get​(java.lang.Object key)
    Returns value of the given key.
    boolean isEmpty()
    Returns true when there is no key / value parity in the HashMap
    V put​(K key, V value)
    Puts given key into the HashMap with it's value
    V remove​(java.lang.Object key)
    Removes given key from HashMap.
    int size()
    Returns number of keys that is available in the HashMap

  • Method Details

    • get

      V get​(java.lang.Object key)
      Returns value of the given key. Returns null if key doesn't exist in the HashMap
      Parameters:
      key - Key that will be searched in the method
      Returns:
      Equivalent value of given key

    • put

      V put​(K key, V value)
      Puts given key into the HashMap with it's value
      Parameters:
      key - Key that will be inserted into the HashMap
      value - Value equivalent of the key
      Returns:
      return old value of the given key if given key already exist

    • remove

      V remove​(java.lang.Object key)
      Removes given key from HashMap. Returns null if given key doesn't exist in the HashMap
      Parameters:
      key - Key that will be removed from the HashMap
      Returns:
      Value equivalent of the key. Null if key doesn't exist.

    • size

      int size()
      Returns number of keys that is available in the HashMap
      Returns:
      Total number of key / values

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Returns true when there is no key / value parity in the HashMap
      Returns:
      True when there is no key / value parity in the HashMap.
